                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/2777: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-26T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 26, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>478. Reference your 770 of July 25. The subject of your telegram has been
                    discussed with the British Embassy here who are telegraphing to London urging
                    that instructions be given to restore the program for joint presentation of the
                    buying programs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
